I am currently running into the above issue when refactoring a project to work with Verilator, specifically using dynamic arrays as an input to a function and then passing in an unpacked array during the function call. I attached a minimal test below which compiles/runs properly with other commercial simulators, and was just wondering how to approach implementing this behavior in Verilator as well. (or is it even a desired behavior?)


```
module test;
    function automatic void dump_regfile (int n, logic [7:0] regarray []);      
    for (int r=0; r<n; r++) begin       
        $display(regarray[r]);
    end
    endfunction

    logic [7:0] ram_dram [8];

    initial begin
        ram_dram = '{8{8'b0}};
        dump_regfile(8, ram_dram);
    end
endmodule
```

